radiographic_examinations.findings: Lung bases clear bilaterally. A 12-mm hypoattenuating lesion at liver dome likely representing a simple cyst. Small hypoattenuating lesion in the upper pole of the spleen measuring 11 mm likely a small hemangioma or cyst. Kidneys homogeneously enhancing with multiple bilateral hypoattenuating lesions too small to further characterize. Appendix fluid-filled and dilated measuring 10 mm with intraluminal appendicolith and periappendiceal fat stranding. No evidence of abscess formation or perforation. No free air or fluid in the peritoneal cavity. Fat-containing left inguinal hernia. No suspicious focal lytic or sclerotic bony lesions.
